The paper discusses the deployment of small cells in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a game theory-based model for resolving interference management and QoS provisioning, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of autonomous and distributed architecture for improving communication systems, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of numerical simulations to demonstrate the efficacy of the proposed model, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the revenue generation for service-providing operators, which is related to game theory (cs.GT).
